description.narrative:
National Environmental Centre aims at increasing the efficiency of the integrated water management approach at the national and local level targeting three directions with a high impact on water:
1) water management itself and work with stakeholders; 
2) waste management;
3) green economy and climate change;
Among expected results of the implementation of the NEC Strategy are:
Increased capacities and vigilance of the decision makers (local public authorities, decentralized authorities in environment and health) in water resources management;
Increased public vigilance and involvement in water resources protection, as well as change of behaviour of water users;
Increased capacities of LPA in integrated water resources management;
Enhanced capacities of the authorities in the implementation of the integrated waste management system;
Increased volume of separately collected waste;
New entrepreneurs willing to set up biomass plantations for bioenergy on degraded lands;
Sustainable agricultural model - School Garden established in the rural areas;
